(sort1000WithNoRecursion)
Please state the status of this question:
1. Incomplete
$2. Solved with testing?$ <-
3. Solved without testing? 
If solved, please BRIEFLY explain your strategy.
    insertion sort compares elements that are consecutively placed.
    this would not be great if it is reverse sorted.

    I simply widened the intervals of comparison so instead of
    comparing elements that are close to each other, enlarge the 
    interval of the elements that are compared and narrow down.

    On average, this would be way better than normal insertion sort.
    interval = 2^k -1
    on every iteration of comparison k
    and do insertion sort with given interval.
