Quiz02_04:
30 points plus up to 20 bonus points
(isAVL and genAVLBST)
Please state the status of this question:
1. Incomplete
2. Solved with testing?
3. Solved without testing?
If solved, please BRIEFLY explain your strategy.

the generated AVL is of maximal height (not minimal height) because
AVL ensures that the difference between the height of 
    1. left subtree and
    2. righ subtree
is {-1,0,1}.
Because of this rule, each node has a minimum number of subtrees that it has
to satisfy the rule.
So the height of lchild is h-1 and that of rchild is h-2
which forms minimum number of nodes at height h = 1 + min(h-1) + min(h-2)

this is fibonacci sequence! and recursive fibonacci sequence would get us
biased or leaned structure of the tree that tends to lean on either sides,
which yields a miximal height instead of minimal height


